Ant IV subdivided into 18 subsegments with 22 whorls, formula is 1 + 16 + 1 = (AI–III) + (M1,16) + (BA + BM + BB), M1 to M16 each with eight chaetae and one or two sensilla, Ant. IV subapical organ present (
Fig. 24
).

Distribution and habitat. Good’s Biogeographic zone 27 ( Good 1974 , Culik & Zeppelini 2003 ). The Köppen’s climate is As ( Köppen 1936 , Shear 1966 ,
Kottek et al. 2006
), with predominance of dry winter and wet summer, mean temperatures of 18°C during winter and 22°C in the summer.
